</head><body><table width=90% align=center><tr><td class=textbody><center><h1>AE Snares</h1><br>by RanthED</center><br> I see many wizards new to quadding casting snare repeatedly until all four are snared so that they feel secure that snare wont break unexpectedly, this is not necessary. When casting AE snare on your 4 mobs in a quad; Snare, Snare, Resist, Resist + Resist, Resist, Snare, Snare = all four mobs snared. The text order stays the same the entire quad (unless you get a fifth or sixth mob added in somehow).</td></tr></table></body></html>